<IFRAME FRAMEBORDER=1 ALIGN=CENTER width=100% HEIGHT=200 SCROLLING=YES SRC="http://boards.stratics.com/forums/Forum174/HTML/000122.html">
<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width="95%"><TR><td bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="100%"><TR bgcolor="#000050"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#FFFFFF" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Jhaelen</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">How do we stop 60th level + characters from soloing Vox?<P>One way is that all new spells and abilities above level 50 only work on the Planes.  That way groups can still kill Vox, but it will still remain a challenge even for a levl 75 character.<P>  While the Planes can have some INSANELY dangerous critters.<P>  Through in armor and weapons that can only be equipped in the planes, and you got the tanks covered as well.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Jezel</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Well we don't know for a fact if the level cap will be raised, and if it is I don't think it will be limited to only people who buy the expansion.<P>I'm sure that if the cap is raised, at least the dragons will get a boost in power, Verant has already said they don't want them soloed, or even taken by a group of 6.<P>------------------<BR>Jezel Dragonblood<BR>Handmaiden of Veeshan</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Kren Lighthammer</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">I don't think raising the dragons powers is fair.  Since I haven't made a mad rush to power lvl to 50, I haven't yet had the opportunity to take on a dragon.  But when I am 50, I want the opportunity to be the same for me as it was to those three months before me.  Why take my time and roleplay if by the time I catch up with powergamers nothing is what it once was.<P>-Kren Lighthammer</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Kinter</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Minor correction:  if you go to the official Ruins of Kunark homepage, one of the features they announce is a higher level cap.  So that's official now -- the expansion will allow players to grow beyond level 50.<BR><P>------------------<BR><BR>Kinter, 25th Circle Halfling Cleric on Prexus.<P>Of COURSE!  I'm ALWAYS willing to help out a generous donor to the church.... *AHEM*<P><BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Kern the Hunter</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">-I say let them Solo her they deserve it.<P>------------------<BR>On the Cazic Thule Server<BR>*Kernan Fenrirson Barbarian Warrior,26th Rank of the Wolves,Naked LongWalk Hating Weilder of the LangSeax.{Highpass Heavy Guards}"For Halas and Glory!"<BR>*Orkus Barbarian Shaman 16th Vision,Spirit Weilding DEMI-GOD in the making.<BR>*Ahirah Dwarven Paladin 9th Tier "Fear me Evil, for I weild the Rantho Rapier!" <P>-"Never argue with an Idiot. First they drag you down to thier level, then beat you with experience." -Unknown</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Cassie - M Marr</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">I firmly believe the reason Verant doesn't want Vox or Nag to be taken in a group of six is simply because of the squabbles that would occur.  The dragons only spawn every seven to eight days now, at random, but they pop every time after a server patch or reset.  Imagine now twelve groups of six all racing to Sol B the minute the server comes back up to get to Nagafen and the KSing that would occur.  It would be chaos.  Verant likes it as it is where it requires 18 to 24 very good players to take out a dragon, since by default on any mature server there are usually only one or two guilds that can do it with success.  Voila, dragons are "uber-mobs" and there is very little competition for their very nice and sought-after loot (except within the group itself).  It's waaaaaaaaay easier to assemble a group of six or eight 55's for a dragon raid than a group of 18 or 24 50s.  Thus unless they twinked the dragons up, these mobs would suddenly be accessible to many, many more players and chaos would reign.  <P>The solution?  Up the spawn on the dragons to three times a day or so.  Drop their loot a bit if you have too (frequency and quality) but not too much.  So what if in six months most 55's are walking around in a cloak of flames?  Right now most 50 casters have runed cowls/SMRs or plane gear and most 50 warrs have mith 2H and some plane armor.  God, we've all seen level 15 twinks dual wielding yaks LOL, and yaks used to be talked about in hushed tones as if mentioning the weapon of God Himself.  I realize dragon/Fear/Hate gear right now is considered elite and tops, but as soon as Air/fill-in-name-of-new-zone-or-plane-here gear becomes available, it will be considered routine.  Sure, Vox and Nag or draco will no longer be the ubermobs they once were but again, so what.  A week into first Beta Emperor Crush was considered just about unkillable hehe and we all got over that.  <P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">G-Man</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">I dont think anyone even a lvl 60 could solo either dragon ever. So Vox is lue to a level 60 by level. Vox would still have at least 8 times the hit points of a level 60 warrior. I think They sould leave Naggy and Vox as they are and add a few new even more powerfull dragons.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE></td></tr></table> 
</IFRAME>
</FONT>
